    <etym xml:lang="ru">Из <ref type="xr" target="#entry_a"/> ‘этот’ и <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_bon"/> ‘день’ (в дигорском — местный падеж); от него adj. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_abonykkon"/> | %iabonikkon%i 'сегодняшний'. Ср. по образованию <mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>a-dyá</w><gloss><q>сегодня</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="yai"><lang/><w>a mét</w><gloss><q>в этот день</q></gloss></mentioned>
                (<bibl><ref target="#ref_KPF"/><biblScope>Abt. III, Bd. II, стр. 229, 390,
                418</biblScope></bibl>). См. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_a"/> и <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_bon"/>; ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_axsæv"/>, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_ībon"/>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">From <ref type="xr" target="#entry_a"/> ‘thisʼ and <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_bon"/> ‘dayʼ (in Digor — locative case); from which adj. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_abonykkon"/> | %iabonikkon%i ‘today'sʼ. Cf. similar derivates: <mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>a-dyá</w><gloss><q>today</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="yai"><lang/><w>a mét</w><gloss><q>on this day</q></gloss></mentioned>
                (<bibl><ref target="#ref_KPF"/><biblScope>Abt. III, Bd. II, pp. 229, 390,
                418</biblScope></bibl>). See <ref type="xr" target="#entry_a"/> and <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_bon"/>; cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_axsæv"/>, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_ībon"/>.</etym>
